{{Quote|By the Fire Rings of Fornax!|[[Rithgar]], cursing|<ref name="Hasty Exit">{{WEGCite|story=Hasty Exit|book=Shadows of the Empire Sourcebook}}</ref>}}
The '''Fire Rings of Fornax''', also known as the '''Five Fire Rings of Fornax''',<ref name="EA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> were one of the natural wonders of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]], in which the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Fornax/Legends|Fornax]] appeared to be encircled by five rings of intense fire.

==History==
{{Quote|Y'know, kid -- getting back to the ''Falcon''{{'s}} going be like flying thru the five Fire Rings of Fornax!|[[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]]|<ref name="Star Wars (1977) 4">[[Star Wars (1977) 4|''Star Wars'' (1977) 4]]</ref>}}
They were actually solar prominences attracted to the planet due to its close proximity to its [[Star/Legends|star]]. [[Pirate/Legends|Pirates]] were known to duel to the death within the rings, so that no combatant could escape unburned.

As the rings were a natural phenomenon instead of being created by intelligent beings, they were not included in the list of the [[Twenty Wonders of the Galaxy]] by the historian [[Vicendi]] in [[10,000 BBY]].<ref name="EA" />
The side order dish [[Fiery Fornax rings|Fornax rings]] was named after the natural phenomena.<ref name="DAD">{{Hyperspace|url=fans/hyperspace/source/dexdiner/index.html|text=Dining at Dex's|int=Dining at Dex's}}</ref>

